23:41.526 --> 23:46.994
He says that in chapter 5, therefore, being justified by faith, we are peace with God

23:47.138 --> 23:58.576
Through our Lord Jesus Christ, now listen, thy womb also, we have access thy faith into this grace wherein we stand.

24:00.399 --> 24:02.462
Some of you may remember when we were dealing with that.

24:02.882 --> 24:09.112
I'd rather remember that I gave a whole evening to that, this standing of the Christian.

24:10.434 --> 24:15.442
That the Christian is a man who is unable to stand in the presence of God.

24:15.586 --> 24:17.608
Now, what do you mean by this standing?

24:17.868 --> 24:23.153
Well, it's the same idea as the psalmist puts before us in the first psalm.

24:24.775 --> 24:38.388
Blessed is the men that walketh not in the council of the ungodly, nor standeth in the way of sinners, nor siteth in the seat of the scornful, but his delight is in the law of the lord and in his lord hath he meditated day and night.

24:39.449 --> 24:44.274
And he shall be like a tree planted by the rivers of water that bringeth forth his fruit in his season.

24:44.546 --> 24:48.271
His leaf also shall not wither, and whatsoever he doeth shall prosper.

24:48.491 --> 24:50.974
Listen, but the ungodly are not so.

24:52.135 --> 24:55.920
But are like the chaff, which the wind drive us away, therefore.

24:57.803 --> 25:00.987
The ungodly shall not stand in the judgment.

25:01.347 --> 25:02.508
That's it.

25:02.528 --> 25:09.057
They shall not stand, nor sinners, in the congregation of the righteous, far from standing.

25:09.437 --> 25:13.362
They are like the chaff, that the wind drive us and blow us away.

25:14.018 --> 25:17.202
This is a tremendous notion that we must never lose sight of.

25:18.864 --> 25:21.528
A Christian is not a man of groves as it were.

25:22.830 --> 25:24.952
A Christian is not a man who is lounging.

25:26.134 --> 25:29.679
Once a man realizes the way of salvation, he stands.

25:31.561 --> 25:36.588
Being justified by faith, we have peace with God.

25:37.008 --> 25:38.290
He's great affirmation.

25:39.298 --> 25:44.526
There is therefore now no condemnation to them that are in Christ Jesus.

25:45.487 --> 25:46.349
That's enough for a mission.

25:47.290 --> 25:48.832
The Christian is a man who stands.

25:50.315 --> 25:51.436
He isn't uncertain.

25:52.137 --> 25:54.120
He isn't hesitant.

25:54.140 --> 25:58.206
He's not as if we're half in and half out, wondering whether he's saved us.

25:58.226 --> 25:58.907
He stands.

25:59.168 --> 26:00.229
We are meant to stand.

26:01.511 --> 26:05.938
And says the apostle, you stand by faith.

26:06.786 --> 26:12.493
And for no other reason whatsoever, you can't stand in the presence of God simply because you're a gentile.

26:13.374 --> 26:17.138
You can't stand in the presence of God simply because you're a good moral person.

26:17.699 --> 26:18.760
It's impossible.

26:18.780 --> 26:23.505
Nobody can stand in the presence of God in his own inherent righteousness.

26:24.306 --> 26:26.008
There is none righteous, no not one.

26:26.529 --> 26:29.352
All have sinned and come short of the glory of God.

26:29.572 --> 26:31.935
The whole world lieeth guilty.

26:32.015 --> 26:32.436
That's it.

26:32.596 --> 26:34.578
Lieeth guilty before God.

26:36.162 --> 26:38.104
But in Christ, you stand.

26:38.364 --> 26:39.125
You don't lie.

26:39.185 --> 26:40.066
You stand.

26:41.408 --> 26:44.571
And so you see, he brings in this wonderful word again.

26:44.631 --> 26:58.046
And I couldn't pass it without emphasizing it and repeating it in this way, in order that you may see that once a man understands this way of salvation, he stands.

26:59.588 --> 27:03.512
He goes with boldness and confidence into the presence of God.

27:03.772 --> 27:05.234
We have this access, he says.

27:05.506 --> 27:10.912
into this grace wherein we stand, or to use the language of Hebrews 1019.

27:11.993 --> 27:17.219
We have boldness to enter into the earliest of all, by the blood of Jesus.

27:18.160 --> 27:29.552
And when the great day of judgment comes, we say, with Count Zinson's office translated by John Wesley, oh, shall I stand in thy great day?

27:31.955 --> 27:34.898
For who ought to make charge

27:34.978 --> 27:38.182
Shall lay, fully absorbed by the island.

27:38.462 --> 27:38.823
That's it.

27:39.304 --> 27:40.165
I shall stand.

27:40.205 --> 27:46.413
Or with toply the terrors of Lord of God with me can have nothing to do.

27:46.953 --> 27:53.302
My saviors, obedience, and blood hide all my transgressions from thee.

27:53.322 --> 27:54.723
Very well, says the apostle.

27:55.124 --> 28:02.994
Realize that you stand as you do, solely by faith and by nothing else.

28:03.778 --> 28:18.904
Very well, there is his direct answer to this auspicious and foolish and arrogant argument of the Gentiles that they have been grafted in because the Jews being unworthy were cut out.

28:20.246 --> 28:24.193
All a matter of their superiority gives a direct answer.

28:24.995 --> 28:29.362
He says, you're denying the whole principle of justification by faith only.

28:29.506 --> 28:34.714
You are showing an elementary ignorance of the whole way of salvation.

28:35.395 --> 28:36.576
But he doesn't leave them at that.

28:38.219 --> 28:41.223
He starts with it, and that is the way to start.

28:42.225 --> 28:44.788
You start by correcting false doctrine.

28:45.870 --> 28:47.713
You enunciate the true doctrine.

28:48.694 --> 28:56.786
But if you've got a pastor's heart like this manhead, and if you're a preacher as he was, you don't just say a thing like that, you

28:57.026 --> 29:02.373
You drive it home, so he proceeds at once in the last part of this twentieth verse to wish you a warning.

29:04.776 --> 29:06.579
Be not high-minded, but fear.

29:09.042 --> 29:10.123
Now he is reprimanding.

29:11.265 --> 29:11.946
They deserve it.

29:14.169 --> 29:20.257
The arrogance of anybody claiming that he is in the Christian Church because of what he is and who he is.

29:20.317 --> 29:24.082
This is not only wrong, it's something worse.

29:24.482 --> 29:30.830
terribly dangerous, so he issues a shop reprimand being a high-minded, but here.

29:33.353 --> 29:53.618
Now, this is always the greatest danger, the danger of being high-minded, the danger of having the wrong view of ourselves, the danger of overestimating ourselves, the danger of thinking that we are better than we are.

29:54.914 --> 29:58.137
And the only antidote to that he tells them is fear.

29:59.238 --> 30:10.230
And he repeats that later by saying, take heed, in verse 21, if God spared not the natural branches, take heed, lest he also spare not thee.

30:11.631 --> 30:18.358
So you see, having put them right with his direct answer on the pure matter of doctrine, he issues this terrific wall.

30:20.740 --> 30:22.482
Beware of being high-minded.

30:23.266 --> 30:27.450
This is a great theme running right through the whole of the Bible.

30:27.551 --> 30:34.958
I hope to, when I come to the teaching, the exposition of the teaching to explain it in greater detail to you.

30:35.099 --> 30:37.942
I'm just explaining the passage for the moment.

30:37.962 --> 30:49.714
So the third thing he does, having now put them right from this question of justification by faith and faith, and then having driven it on with the warning and the reprimand

30:49.890 --> 30:56.359
He then produces an unanswerable argument, which is going to put this matter right once and forever, in verse 21.

30:56.479 --> 30:58.422
And here it is.

31:00.345 --> 31:09.478
If God is scared not the natural branches, take heed, lest he also scare not thee.

31:11.221 --> 31:13.223
Why do I say that this is unanswerable?

31:13.264 --> 31:14.245
Well, I'll go further.

31:14.686 --> 31:17.810
I'll say that at this point the apostle simply demolishes

31:18.082 --> 31:21.846
this foolish case put up by the Gentiles in their ignorance.

31:24.048 --> 31:25.409
He demolishes it completely.

31:25.669 --> 31:26.410
How does he do so?

31:26.950 --> 31:32.736
Well, he again takes up what is obviously his favorite formula.

31:33.697 --> 31:35.439
We've seen him doing it so after.

31:37.140 --> 31:40.383
If the formula which says, if this, then that.

31:41.705 --> 31:43.246
This is sure logic, of course.

31:43.947 --> 31:47.410
And the apostle was a master at logic.

31:47.874 --> 31:53.382
This be true very well then, this follows, take heed.

31:53.402 --> 31:53.923
What is this?

31:54.123 --> 31:57.508
Well, this is the argument again from the greater to the lesser.

31:59.111 --> 32:01.875
Or we found him doing this almost endlessly.

32:02.616 --> 32:06.922
One of my favorite illustrations of his doing this is Romans 5-10.

32:08.825 --> 32:14.834
For if, when we were enemies, we were reconciled to God by the death of his son,

32:15.522 --> 32:19.088
How much more or much more being reconciled?

32:19.408 --> 32:21.051
We shall be saved by his life.

32:21.411 --> 32:25.217
If God has done the greatest thing, he can't fail to do the lesser thing.

32:25.237 --> 32:26.680
It's the same kind of argument here.

32:29.164 --> 32:33.851
Well, what is this greater thing and what is this lesser thing to which I am referring?

32:34.352 --> 32:34.873
Well, it's this.

32:36.295 --> 32:37.497
And there is no answer to this.

32:39.761 --> 32:43.186
If God spared not the natural branches,

32:44.866 --> 33:09.330
If in other words, God has taken out of this olive tree, the Jew, who were the natural branches, who were his own people, the people that he had created himself, for himself, for his own peculiar possession, if God has dealt with them because of their arrogant pride in their nationality,

33:09.538 --> 33:14.726
by taking them out of the olive tree and casting them aside, if he's done that with them of old people?

33:17.090 --> 33:32.233
Well, to put it at its very lowest, it shouldn't surprise us if he does that with people who've been brought in in an unnatural manner and were not his own original people.

33:33.555 --> 33:34.276
That's the argument.

33:35.158 --> 33:36.460
Let me put it you like this.

33:36.760 --> 33:37.842
Charles Hodge, I think,

33:38.018 --> 33:39.921
deals with this in a most excellent manner.

33:41.803 --> 33:44.207
It's an argument, if you like, in this way.

33:46.430 --> 34:06.738
Imagine a man who had got a son, and of course, he looked to this son to carry on his business, his affairs, and his tradition, and he lavished his love upon him, and he blessed him, and he did everything he could for his good pleasure and for his well-being.

34:08.162 --> 34:13.089
But unfortunately, this son turns out to be a poor character.

34:14.210 --> 34:19.898
Misbehaves himself, insults his father, does everything contrary to his father's will.

34:20.519 --> 34:24.304
And the father can see the whole of his purpose going astray.

34:26.127 --> 34:30.693
And he feels this to such an extent that he puts his son on one side.

34:30.813 --> 34:37.202
And he takes, if you like, a servant or somebody whom he knows, or somebody else's son with whom he's acquainted,

34:37.346 --> 34:41.573
and he adopts these other men and puts him into the position of his son.

34:41.613 --> 34:45.759
Now, this is the apostle's argument.

34:45.779 --> 35:02.866
He says, if this man is such a man and such a righteous man and has got such a view of his own purpose, that he even puts his own natural son on one side, you be very careful as the adopted son.

35:03.778 --> 35:12.779
If he will put his naturals on one side because of his ill behavior, how much more so is he likely to do it with you?

35:13.961 --> 35:16.327
Now that's the argument, and it's the most powerful argument.

35:16.648 --> 35:18.111
It is an unanswerable argument.

35:18.351 --> 35:21.559
He here demolishes the case of the Gentiles once and forever.

35:21.799 --> 35:22.962
Look here, says Paul.

35:23.106 --> 35:34.581
it was because of their arrogant pride in themselves that God has put aside the Jews, the people whom he prepared for himself, if he's done that with them, how much more so?

35:36.042 --> 35:45.474
Will he do that with people like you, Gentiles, who come in from the outside and have been grafted in this as it were unnatural men.

35:46.115 --> 35:49.460
Now, that is the argument I say from the greater to the lesser.

35:49.480 --> 35:51.442
It is the argument

35:52.514 --> 35:58.720
from what God has already done to what he will inevitably do with others who are in a life situation in position.

35:59.721 --> 36:17.198
And because of the fact, and because it is the greatest, the greatest of all, it is, I say, something that completely demolishes this wrong and false argument which has been put forward here by this Gentile objector.

36:17.218 --> 36:21.362
Well, there is the third way in which he deals with this position.

36:22.370 --> 36:39.646
And then, fourthly, in verse 22, he goes on to draw a great deduction from all this with regard to the character of God and God's ways with respect to men.

36:40.287 --> 36:41.068
Now, here it is.

36:41.728 --> 36:52.178
Behold, therefore, the goodness and severity of God on them which fell, severity.

36:52.706 --> 37:03.216
But toward the goodness, if thou continuing his goodness, otherwise thou also shalt be cut and cut off.

37:04.557 --> 37:07.760
Now, here is, of course, a great general statement.

37:09.502 --> 37:13.025
And as I say, it is a kind of deduction.

37:13.045 --> 37:22.354
That's why he starts by saying, behold, therefore, in the light of what God has actually done, this is the only conclusion to which we can come.

37:24.450 --> 37:27.854
In other words, he lifts up the whole argument to this position.

37:30.416 --> 37:40.327
Men become bestful and proud and despise others in the Kingdom of God for one reason only.

37:41.588 --> 37:48.776
And that is that they fail to realize the truth about God himself.

37:48.796 --> 37:50.418
That's what it all ultimately comes to.

37:52.418 --> 37:56.702
This is the root cause of nearly all our troubles.

37:58.184 --> 38:01.607
I want to show you this in greater detail when we come to the teaching.

38:01.887 --> 38:05.110
I'm simply explaining his statement to you this evening.

38:05.811 --> 38:09.835
Here it is, he says, how has it become possible?

38:09.875 --> 38:17.762
How is it conceivable that anybody should burst in the presence of God, whether Jew or Gentile?

38:18.743 --> 38:21.426
There's only one answer.

38:21.570 --> 38:30.099
that they have failed to understand the truth about God, about his nature, about his character, about his attributes.

38:31.721 --> 38:36.045
And often he says, nothing is more important than that you should be clear about this.

38:36.205 --> 38:40.390
God has revealed the truth concerning himself.

38:40.410 --> 38:48.178
And for this particular object we are dealing with here, he has revealed not only his goodness, but also his severity.

38:50.210 --> 39:13.563
and men and women get into trouble, always, because instead of teaching the revelation of the character of God in these ways with respect to men, as we have it revealed in the Bible, they substitute their own ideas for that, or they take a part of the teaching of the Bible and they reject the remainder.

39:14.605 --> 39:18.450
Now, it will be my object when we come to the teaching.

39:18.658 --> 39:25.146
the doctrine involved in this statement to work that out with you in detail.

39:25.166 --> 39:29.952
But you can think immediately for yourselves, oh, this is so applicable at this present time.

39:31.494 --> 39:42.027
We are living in an age when the people even justify the fact that they never attend the place of worship at all on the grounds that God is love.

39:44.049 --> 39:48.114
They justify immorality in the same way, God is love.

39:48.386 --> 39:50.428
There's no such thing as the wrath of God.

39:50.688 --> 39:51.749
There is no justice.

39:51.769 --> 39:52.890
There is no severity.

39:54.112 --> 39:56.714
That's the very thing that is happening at the present time.

39:58.076 --> 40:05.002
Men and women who believe in God, so they say they don't believe in God as he's revealed himself.

40:05.022 --> 40:06.384
They've got partial notions.

40:06.764 --> 40:07.805
They pick and choose.

40:08.286 --> 40:09.327
They accept what they like.

40:09.407 --> 40:10.688
They reject what they don't like.

40:11.449 --> 40:13.511
In other words, they don't worship God at all.

40:13.811 --> 40:16.914
They worship an image which they themselves have erected.

40:17.698 --> 40:26.108
and there are others of course, who go still further, who instead of taking the biblical revelation in any sense, discard it completely.

40:26.969 --> 40:33.437
And in terms of philosophy and so on, construct a God after their own image and say that this is God.

40:34.779 --> 40:44.430
And obviously therefore, they are wrong in the whole of their thinking and become wrong, likewise in their behavior and in their conduct.

40:44.650 --> 40:47.634
Well now, there is the exposition

40:49.314 --> 40:53.261
of what the Apostle says about this whole mapper.

40:53.281 --> 40:55.004
I'm afraid we've got to leave it at that.

40:56.847 --> 41:02.376
We haven't the time even to begin with the teaching that is involved in all this.

41:02.536 --> 41:06.764
We've simply dealt with my first big section.

41:09.068 --> 41:12.854
Get this fact clearly into your mind as to what the Apostle is saying here.

41:13.515 --> 41:15.218
He is dealing with people.

41:16.770 --> 41:23.198
who say, we are Christians because of something that is inherently true about us.

41:25.601 --> 41:38.817
That's the thing that he's dealing with, the Gentiles, like the Jews before them, imagining that they were in simply because they're such good people, because they're superior to others and so on and so forth.

41:38.837 --> 41:41.260
That's the thing he's dealing with.

41:41.280 --> 41:45.906
He's dealing with people who think they're Christians because they've been born in Great Britain and not in India.

41:47.330 --> 41:52.157
He's dealing with people who think that they're Christians because they were Christians or baptized, it doesn't matter which.

41:53.198 --> 42:00.949
He's dealing with people who think they're Christians because of the good life they've lived or because of their excellent natural moral characters.

42:02.330 --> 42:05.895
He's dealing with people who are boasting about anything at all.

42:08.479 --> 42:10.602
That's what he's dealing with.

42:10.622 --> 42:11.944
And you notice what he says.

42:14.066 --> 42:16.690
He says, this is all due to the fact

42:18.178 --> 42:21.723
that you have misunderstood that salvation is by faith alone.

42:23.565 --> 42:27.631
This basic principle, it's a denial of that.

42:29.053 --> 42:47.538
And still more, it is a failure to realize the truth about God, that the only thing that matters is our relationship to God, and that that is always a matter of faith.

42:48.226 --> 42:48.667
Very well.

42:48.787 --> 42:54.314
God willing, we'll proceed with our discussion of the teaching next Friday evening.

42:54.695 --> 42:55.275
Let us pray.

42:55.316 --> 43:02.405
Oh Lord, God, we pray thee to look down upon us with mercy and with compassion.

43:03.486 --> 43:14.942
We have been considering this statement concerning the first Gentiles who came into the Christian church and we see so much of the same thing by nature in ourselves.

43:15.943 --> 43:18.066
Oh God, we acknowledge

43:18.274 --> 43:27.326
more than ever that we see clearly that we are saved by grace through faith, and that not of ourselves it is the gift of God.

43:27.346 --> 43:37.420
O Lord, open our understandings, we pray the enablers especially to heed the warning of thy word, be not high-minded but fear.

43:37.440 --> 43:45.170
O Lord, by thy spirit apply this great truth to us one by one.

43:45.602 --> 43:51.430
that it may save us from grievous error, and all that follows from such error.

43:52.191 --> 43:59.501
Keep us, we pray, as little children, keep us to that simplicity, which is in Christ Jesus.

44:00.542 --> 44:10.756
And now, may the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ and the love of God and the fellowship and the communion of the Holy Spirit abide and continue with us.

44:10.937 --> 44:12.018
Now, this night,

44:12.514 --> 44:20.145
The words that remain under this are short and certain earthly life and pilgrimage and evermore.

44:21.912 --> 44:22.354
Amen.

